Class WebCryptoWrappedKey

An AES-GCM symmetric key in raw formatted encrypted using an RSA-OAEP public key. We use a symmetrically derived key for the shared secret instead of just random numbers. There are two reasons for this.

First, WebCrypto treats CryptoKeys specially in that the material is can be setup to never be exposed the application, so when we generate these secrets, we can hide them from JS by declaring them non-extractable or usable for wrapping or encrypting only.

Secondly, we eventually want to move off of RSA-OAEP and use ECDH, and ECDH doesn't support encryption or wrapping of randomly generated bits.
